the previous low serial number was # 1052 .

title: For Sale:  1968 Winchester Model 70 30-06 w/ Weaver V9 optic
postcontent:
Classic "Rifleman's Rifle" Winchester model 70 chambered in 30-06. Manufactured in 1968, when Winchester corrected many of the negatives introduced in the 1964 model.

 "In 1968 further revisions were made to the Model 70 in part to address consumer concerns.[9] An "anti-bind" feature was introduced to make operation of the action smoother, which comprised a groove in an extended right locking lug operating on a rib on the right side of the receiver. This made the action noticeably smoother to operate and has been retained to the present day. A steel floorplate and stainless magazine follower were introduced, partially revoking changes introduced in the 1964 model. The alloy trigger guard was retained."

Remarkable rifle that shoots beautifully, and the scope is true to form and age- but in great condition. Truly a classic and comes with comfy Butler Creek sling, as well as a Butler Creek glass cover (back only, front does not fit with rear iron sight). Mine comes with the original 6 round magazine, plus 2 additional 6 round magazines, plus an 8 round magazine. All 4 magazines are original Kimber (no aftermarket cheapies). It also comes with the factory Kimber softcase, a brand new Kimber gun lock, manual, and the original box it came in. I got this Kimber to conceal carry because my HK P30 was just a little too big. With a barrel length of just 2.7 inches, Solo pistols are easy to carry and conceal. Many of the features borrowed from 1911 pistols also make them exceptionally safe.
